# ai-literature-os — example crontab
#
# Edit your crontab with `crontab -e` and uncomment the lines you want.
# Substitute $REPO with your actual clone path (e.g. ~/Projects/ai-literature-os)
# and $HOME with your actual home dir if cron resolves it differently on your
# system.
#
# CRITICAL ORDERING (Pipeline Contract item 5): if you have other QMD
# collections (e.g. an Obsidian vault on top of the science vault), the
# other-collection re-embed cron MUST run AFTER the science-vault re-embed.
# `qmd embed --collection` is silently ignored upstream
# (https://github.com/tobi/qmd/issues/558). Cron ordering is the only safety net.
#
# All times below assume your local timezone (whatever `date` reports).
# Adjust as needed.

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vault pipeline — nightly sync
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Convert new sources, deduplicate, enrich, integrate, re-embed, relate,
# cluster, re-index. Idempotent; safe to run nightly even if nothing changed.
# Logs: $LOG_DIR/sync-vault.log (defaults to /tmp/sync-vault.log)
# 0 0 * * * $REPO/vault-pipeline/scripts/sync-vault.sh >> $HOME/.cache/sync-vault.log 2>&1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (Optional) Other-collection re-embed — MUST run AFTER the vault sync
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment and customize if you have a second QMD collection (e.g. a personal
# Obsidian vault). It runs at 1 AM, after the midnight vault sync.
# 0 1 * * * cd /path/to/your/other/collection && qmd update && qmd embed --collection brain >> $HOME/.cache/other-embed.log 2>&1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vault librarian — Tue/Fri 4 AM health check
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Writes a health report to your vault for review. The agent definition lives
# in claude-code-agents/vault-librarian.md and runs via `claude -p` with a
# small prompt. See agent file for the report path it expects.
# 0 4 * * 2,5 $CLAUDE_BIN -p "run the vault-librarian agent" --output-format text >> $HOME/.cache/vault-librarian.log 2>&1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (Optional) Research digest — Sunday 4 AM
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Polls PubMed + bioRxiv + NIH Reporter, scores against your researcher
# profile, writes to Supabase. Skip this whole block if you're not using
# the research digest.
# 0 4 * * 0 cd $REPO/research-digest/pipeline && node scripts/poll-journals.js --commit --score >> $HOME/.cache/digest-papers.log 2>&1
# 5 4 * * 0 cd $REPO/research-digest/pipeline && node scripts/poll-grants.js   --commit --score >> $HOME/.cache/digest-grants.log 2>&1
# 30 4 * * 0 cd $REPO/research-digest/pipeline && node scripts/score-with-claude.js papers      >> $HOME/.cache/digest-score-papers.log 2>&1
# 45 4 * * 0 cd $REPO/research-digest/pipeline && node scripts/score-with-claude.js grants      >> $HOME/.cache/digest-score-grants.log 2>&1

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Notes on cron and the Claude CLI
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - Cron has a minimal PATH and no shell rc files. Set PATH at the top of the
#   crontab (above) and use absolute paths to binaries via env vars in .env
#   ($CLAUDE_BIN, $REPO).
# - Source $HOME/.config/ai-literature-os.env at the start of any wrapper
#   script, OR set the env vars directly in the crontab above.
# - If you use nvm-managed Node, set $CLAUDE_BIN to the absolute path of the
#   `claude` binary inside the relevant nvm version directory.
